  "issue_title": "feature: add get_foreground_app tool",
  "issue_body": "Parent: #75\n\n## Problem\n\nTool verification needs to know which app/window is currently foreground, but TouchPilot does not expose a dedicated foreground-app inspection tool.\n\nThis makes `open_app`, `press_back`, `press_home`, and future multi-step loops harder to verify.\n\n## Proposed behavior\n\nAdd a `get_foreground_app` Android tool that returns current foreground package/window information where Android allows it.\n\nThe result should include, when available:\n\n- package name,\n- app label,\n- window title,\n- activity/class if accessible,\n- whether TouchPilot AccessibilityService is connected.\n\n## User workflow\n\nA user or local agent can ask TouchPilot where it is before or after an action, and verification can use the result to confirm transitions.\n\n## Local-first impact\n\nForeground state is local device context and is necessary for reliable local control.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\n\nForeground app metadata can reveal private app usage. Keep logs concise, avoid sensitive text, and do not require broad new permissions unless clearly justified.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Add `get_foreground_app` to the Android tool catalog.\n- [ ] Return package/window/app label where practical.\n- [ ] Do not add unnecessary permissions.\n- [ ] Use result in or prepare for post-action verification.\n- [ ] Add unit tests for result shape and fallback behavior.\n- [ ] Add live checklist coverage.\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\nInfer foreground app from raw screen dumps only. Rejected because verification needs a stable structured signal.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-27T15:07:48.000Z",
